Class FinalFilter<O>

    public class FinalFilter<O>
extends Filter<O,O>
    A special type of Filter that collects the results it is told to process in a List so they can be obtained.

    FT_7

      • clone

        public FinalFilter<O> clone()
        Description copied from class: Filter
        Returns a Filter of the same type as this Filter, processing input from the same queue and adding the results to the same FilterScaler. N.B. This method can be inconsistent with Object.equals(java.lang.Object) and Object.hashCode().
        Specified by:
        clone in class Filter<O,O>
        Throws:
        java.lang.UnsupportedOperationException - because a FinalFilter should not be cloned, because usage in a FilterScaler that clones this Filter would cause the results to spread over the Lists collected by these Filters
        See Also:
        Filter.copyNextAndQueue(Filter, Filter)
